Redescription . Body (
Figs. 105–106
) elongate, around 1.3 x longer than wide, integument shining, except for anterior margin of gibbosity; setae yellowish-brown. Vertex with long, sparse and erect setae; deep and dense punctation. Coronal suture with yellowish-brown ellipsoid spot. Frontoclypeus strongly sclerotized, with a subtle median groove

